The William M. Ladd Collection
Gift of Herschel V. Jones, 1916
text: At first glance, this flock may look like it alighted randomly, but some patterns can be discerned among the reeds. Several groups of birds form V shapes, and other birds are paired, including the two staring into the water at the left. The nearest duck echoes an image Bracquemond had created decades earlier for the journal L’Artiste.
title: Reeds and Teal
